ebia.com','Process – Cashless Hospitalisation \n1.	Employee can avail cashless treatment for any planned/emergency hospitalisation in the network hospitals. \n2.	Employee can download the list of the network hospitals from the Start Health Insurance portal. https://www.starhealth.in/network-hospitals\n3.	Pre -Authorization forms are available at the TPA desk of the network hospital. \n4.	The helpdesk representative takes the required information from the Employee and the hospital fills the pre-authorization form. The form is subsequently sent for approval to Star Health Insurance\n5.	Upon receiving the information, the TPA will forward for the initial approval, within a Turn Around Time (TAT) of 3 hours. \n6.	Upon receiving clarification from the hospital, the TPA forwards its approval. \n7.	On the day of the patient’s discharge from the hospital, the hospital dispatches the final bill to the TPA for approval \n8.	Upon verifying the final bill, the TPA forwards its approval to the hospital within its TAT of 3 hours. \n9.	Upon receiving the TPA’s approval of the final bill, the hospital discharges the patient. \n\nProcess – Non Cashless Hospitalisation \n1.	Employee can avail treatment for any planned/emergency hospitalization in non-network hospitals by paying first and claiming the reimbursement later. \n2.	The Employee/ Employee’s family is required to intimate Star Health Insurance about the Employee’s treatment in a non-network hospital, within 48 hours. This mandatory for claim reimbursement.\n3.	The claim form and original bills (Discharge Summary, Investigation Bills/Reports, etc.) are to be submitted to Admin Department within 15 days of the patient’s discharge from the hospital. \n4.	Employee would be required to download the reimbursement form. Link for the form https://www.starhealth.in/sites/default/files/CLAIMFORM.pdf.\n5.	The TPA will process and settle the Employee’s claim reimbursement within 25 days of the receipt of the document provided the documents submitted are complete. \n6.	In case of any discrepancy in claim document, the TPA will send a letter to the Employee, asking for the document to be provided within 15 days. \n7.	In case the Insurance Company does not receive the required document, it will send a reminder to the Employee. \n8.	If the Employee fails to submit the required documents despite two notifications, the Insurance Company is authorised to close the claim and stop further processing. \nSteps to Download E-Card\n1.	Click on the link- www.portal.starhealth.in/Agent/NewGen/GenerateIdCard.aspx\n2.	Enter below policy numbers\n3.	Policy no. P/161130/01/2021/054568 for Employee, Spouse & Kids cards.\n4.	Policy no. P/161130/01/2021/060929 for Parents cards.\n5.	Enter employee id of employee for both the policy cards (E Code in Capital Letter)\n6.	Enter DOB of Employee for employee policy cards & enter DOB of parent for Parent policy cards (DOB of the eldest Parent)   \n7.	In case you have enrolled both set of parents then you have to download the card twice \n\n',11540),(9848,'diwakar.tiwari@xebia.com','2021-09-08 13:34:33','2021-09-08 13:34:33','diwakar.tiwari@xebia.com','After update the bios & driver issue has been fixed I am closing the call As per user confirmation on teams. ',11516),(9849,'suneel.kumar@xebia.com','2021-09-09 00:04:14','2021-09-09 00:04:14','suneel.kumar@xebia.com','done',11495),(9850,'tushar.kaushik@xebia.com','2021-09-09 03:25:08','2021-09-09 03:25:08','tushar.kaushik@xebia.com','Hi Kritika Budhori,\nyou have raised the ticket for Photoshop but it\'s license software\nyou need to raise the ticket below category. Please close this ticket and raise new ticket for Photoshop.\n \nDepartment :-  IT\nClassifications :-  Request\nSub Issue :-   Laptop\nSub Category :-     License software',11502),(9851,'aman.gupta1@xebia.com','2021-09-09 04:40:08','2021-09-09 04:40:08','aman.gupta1@xebia.com','Given!',11428),(9852,'garima.dixit@xebia.com','2021-09-09 04:48:40','2021-09-09 04:48:40